Sooo good! Homemade pasta and the empanadas, awesome! The staff was very nice and helpful. Everything they recommended was fantastic, you can't go wrong. The menu was all inclusive- food, drink and dessert. It was nice to take a break from the Tapas and have some great local food. I just wished I came here sooner than later. The atmosphere is a quaint little hide-away. Nothing fancy, just good food.
